#Text=Fatal police helicopter crash in Slovakia due to technical failure : preliminary Interior Ministry finding
#Text=Sunday , May 21 , 2017
#Text=Last week 's police helicopter accident in eastern Slovakia was caused by technical failure and not human error , said the Ministry of Interior of the Slovak Republic on Friday .
#Text=The statement is based on preliminary flight recorder data analysis .
#Text=Ministry spokesperson Petar Lazarov confirmed the flight recorder and remains of the helicopter will be sent to the United States for further analysis .

#Text=Helicopter crash occurred during a training exercise on May 10 shortly before 2:30 PM CEST at Prešov Air Base near Prešov , resulting in deaths of two crewmembers and serious injuries of both pilots .
#Text=Slovak police helicopter Bell 429 , registration OM-BYM , in August 2015 .
#Text=Image : Puki301 .
#Text=According to initial reports by the Slovak Police Force , the helicopter spiraled down from a height of about 100 metres and 200 metres away from the point of take-off .
#Text=Slovak tabloid newspaper Plus Jeden Deň wrote that , according to a source from the forensic team that analysed flight recorders data , both rotors failed at the same time .

#Text=The accident caused fatal injuries to two Fire and Rescue Corps firefighters , First Lieutenant ( ( sk))Slovak language : ‍nadporučík Peter Toďor , born 1974 , and Lieutenant Colonel ( ( sk))Slovak language : ‍podplukovník
#Text=Radoslav Lacko , born 1968 .
#Text=According to reports , one died on the site , and one in the Louis Pasteur University Hospital in Košice . " The patient suffered serious head and chest injuries .

column1: #Text=Bell Helicopter reacted on the incident , expressing condolences and willingness to assist with the investigation .
#Text=Members of the National Council started their late-afternoon session on May 10 with a minute of silence for the victims of the crash .
#Text=Other government officials expressed their condolences as well , including the President Andrej Kiska , the Prime Minister Robert Fico , and the Mayor of Prešov Andrea Turčanová .
#Text=This accident was not the first Bell 429 helicopter crash in Slovakia .
#Text=On September 7 of last year , an Air-Transport Europe rescue helicopter crashed near Banská Bystrica , killing all three crewmen and a patient aboard .
#Text=Investigation is still in progress and no preliminary results are known .
